The paper deals with graph theory and provides proofs for theorems related to graph properties such as girth, minimum degree, and average degree. The use of entropy in the proofs suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as well as numerical analysis (cs.NA) in the form of inequalities. The theorems are related to graph algorithms and optimization, which could fall under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper deals with bipartite graphs, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
